{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos18.erdos_18a https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos18.erdos_18a.","id":"vf_90921f047eaafd06","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #18: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. We call $m$ practical if every integer $n<m$ is the sum of distinct divisors of $m$. If $m$ is practical then let $h(m)$  be such that $h(m)$ many divisors always suffice.\n\nAre there infinitely many practical $m$ such that\\[h(m) < (\\log\\log m)^{O(1)}?\\]Is it true that $h(n!)<n^{o(1)}$? Or perhaps even $h(n!)<(\\log n)^{O(1)}$? Prize: no. OEIS: A005153. Tags: divisors, factorials, number theory.","id":"vf_ea911c7b75a654e8","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős #18: 6 is a practical number (Erdos18.practicalH_six). Kernel-clean Lean proof — axioms {propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound}, no sorryAx — via le_antisymm. Produced by the vela prover-in-the-loop foundry; verified by the Lean kernel.","claimed_status":"","classification":"importable_attempt","id":"vat_0cd8d57beb510c6d","kind":"theorem","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":["lean_kernel","order_antisymmetry"],"named_obstructions":["asymptotic_practical_number_questions"],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":["The finite value practicalH 6 = 2 does not establish the asymptotic parts of Erdős 18."],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_0cd8d57beb510c6d","trust":"signed"},{"accepted":false,"claim":"Pinned Formal Conjectures activity classification; integration activity does not establish mathematical truth.","id":"activity:fc-mathematical_proof_work:18","kind":"mathematical_proof_work","lifecycle":"banked","source_ref":"sources/formal-conjectures-activity.yaml#problem-18","trust":"declared"}],"activity_types":["theorem"],"attempt_count":1,"ba